  <entry>
    <title>Article Images</title>
    <link href="http://photon-platform.net/uncategorized/article-images/"/>
    <id>http://photon-platform.net/uncategorized/article-images/</id>
    <published>2018-05-11T22:34:21.000Z</published>
    <updated>2018-07-11T23:43:13.000Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Every article can have a dedicated figure - used as the “hero” image and a gallery.<br>  <a id="more"></a></p><p>Photon is configured to create a corresponding asset folder when a new article is created.</p><p>place your full size images in this folder - no need to resize, Photon will take care of it when generating the site.</p><p>use hyphenated names for SEO</p><p>when site is generated, the <a href="https://github.com/i-am-phi/hexo-filter-responsive-images" title="Hexo-Filter-Responsive-Images Plugin on Github" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Responsive Images</a> plugin for Hexo will take care of multiple resized versions of the image in the  generated output</p><p>setting for the default theme</p><p>  </p><p class="code-caption" data-lang="" data-line_number="backend" data-trim_indent="backend" data-label_position="outer" data-labels_left="code" data-labels_right=":" data-labels_copy=""><span class="code-caption-label"></span></p><p></p><pre><code>responsive_images:  pattern: &#39;**/*.+(png|jpg|jpeg)&#39;  sizes:    th:      width: 600    wb:      width: 1920      options:        withoutEnlargement: true</code></pre>]]></content>
    
    <summary type="html">
    
      &lt;p&gt;Every article can have a dedicated figure - used as the “hero” image and a gallery.&lt;br&gt;
    
    </summary>
    
    
      <category term="articles" scheme="http://photon-platform.net/tags/articles/"/>
    
  </entry>
  
